results.name: Array A(x,y): (read as A(0,0), A(1,0), A(0,1), A(2,0), A(1,1), A(0,2), A(3,0), A(2,1), A(1,2), A(0,3),...) Position of the composition A089840[y] o A089840[x] in the table A089840.
comment: This is a "multiplication table" of an infinite enumerable group. Each row and column is a permutation of A001477.
link: A. Karttunen, C-program for computing the elements of this table
example: A(2,1)=14 because A089840[2] = A072796, A089840[1] = A069770 and the composition A069770 o A072796 (here the right hand side permutation acts first) yields A073269 = A089840[14]. Similarly A(2,2)=0, as A089840[2] = A072796, which being an involution, yields A001477 (= A089840[0]) when "squared".
xref: Column 1: A089837, row 1: A089838, the main diagonal: A089841.
